New_York_City_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York City marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its allure\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"many track stars\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4312}, {\"ngram\": \"the prospect\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4345}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4367}, {\"ngram\": \"a bid\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4376}, {\"ngram\": \"larger prize funds\", \"from\": 4381, \"to\": 4399}, {\"ngram\": \"its winners\", \"from\": 4433, \"to\": 4444}, {\"ngram\": \"increased exposure\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4477}, {\"ngram\": \"the roads\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cairess at just 26 could fall into that category, even though his strength, built from the mud-sapping conditions of British cross-country running, lends itself to the longer-distance races.\", \"from\": 4492, \"to\": 4682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4609, \"end\": 4616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999420908658608, \"rank\": 3.086170344983843e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that category\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4540}, {\"ngram\": \"his strength\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4566}, {\"ngram\": \"the mud-sapping conditions\", \"from\": 4579, \"to\": 4605}, {\"ngram\": \"the longer-distance races\", \"from\": 4656, \"to\": 4681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was just nine seconds back and runner-up to Jakob Ingebrigtsen at the 2022 European cross country championships.\", \"from\": 4683, \"to\": 4798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4730, \"end\": 4748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource